<title>USA: Litton wins German fighter navigation deal.</title>
<headline>Litton wins German fighter navigation deal.</headline>
<dateline>WOODLAND HILLS, Calif. 1996-09-04</dateline>
<text>
<p>Litton Industries Inc said it has won a $4.0 million contract, which could rise to a total of $50 million, to supply the navigational system for the German Tornado fighter aircraft.</p>
<p>The German Ministry of Defense, through a three-country consortium called Panavia that includes Britain and Italy, directed British Aerospace Plc to choose Litton.</p>
<p>British Aerospace is the Tornado's navigation equipment authority.</p>
<p>The development contract includes 10 pre-production systems, but includes options for up to 700 production systems if Britain and Italy also choose to upgrade their Tornados.</p>
<p>Deliveries will begin in mid-1997 for laboratory integration. Flight tests will be conducted during 1998, and full-scale production is scheduled to start in 1999.</p>
